Dr. Ehud Ur, professor of medicine at Dalhousie University in Halifax, Nova Scotia, and chairman of the clinical and scientific department of the Canadian Diabetes Association, cautioned that the research was still in its infancy.
Like some other experts, he expressed skepticism as to whether it would be possible to cure diabetes, and pointed out that the findings had no relevance for people who already had Type 1 diabetes.
