You have discovered that the sun works on the same basic principles as other stars: It has been discovered that the activity of all stars in the system is driven by their luminosity, rotation, and nothing else.
To determine the Rossby number of a star, which is related to the plasma flow, the luminosity and the rotation are taken into account together.
The smaller the Rossby number is, the less active the star is in terms of reversals of the magnetic field.
