The 802.11n standard runs on the frequencies 2.4 Ghz and 5.0 Ghz.
This allows it to be backward compatible with 802.11a, 802.11b and 802.11g, provided the base station has dual radio.
The speed of 802.11 n is much faster than that of its predecessors, which had a maximum theoretical throughput of 600 Mbit/s.
