“We will strive to reduce carbon dioxide emissions per unit of GDP by 2020 significantly below the 2005 level,” Hu said.
He did not give a figure for the cuts, but said they would be based on China's economic performance.
He encouraged developing countries to avoid the old path of first polluting and then cleaning up.
He added that “they should not, however, be called upon to enter into commitments that go beyond their level of development, their responsibility and their capabilities”.
